column5: o man ... that seems to be a close one between Cudz and GB. Both of them have great pose and expressions lol ... i vote for a tie
Since it was mentioned in the opening post....here she is again....
Odd..
looks like we've got a 3-way tie now with Stoty in the mix!
Even holding up to the camera doesn't make it look big.  I had to call in the guy who is used to handling such small things...
What can I say ... it was not this minnow's day when I accidently hooked on it
wow...now that really is a (non) trophy too fishing for life...nice.  think we might have to have different species sections on here soon.
Was mine the smallest fish?
I threw my little jackfish outta the live well cuz i caught this upgrader fish!!!!
k here's mine no trophy but i like the pose

Hi Everyone,  After seeing a couple of pics of tiny fish on CCMT's post requesting pics for a 'special project' (intriguing) i could not help remembering some of the little guys i caught, Stoty's tiny bass is very cool and just thought you guys must all have some not so Trophy pics...would be fun to see them. Here's a couple i have. One is a tiny Pike that really hammered a mepps spinner and one of my wife with a GIANT Walleye.
Lol.  I've caught some of them monsters before.  Man, I wish I had some pics to post but only got my digital camera this Christmas.  They'll be rolling in soon enough.
My personal worst pike ever.
Lake trout from this past winter, what was it thinking?? Lure is 3 inches long.

Yep....Tbayboy got a nice one with my HUGE catch...but believe it or not, it wasn't my smallest.  My season opener for 2007 was a good one, with me landing this monster perch.  My 5 year old and I had a competition on catching fish....I lost big time.
Great pics guys, MONSTERS!!!
~~~Ain't caught it yet, the way my soft water phishen been, this is my largest
This is my smallest fish yet   I WISH........Buddy caught that musky lastyear in the moria river
definitely not the smallest i've caught, but the smallest i have a picture of...
Oh man, i'd kill to have 1 like this in the aquarium...
theres mine
not mine but a buddies.    Andrew, you da man.
I think so far, that GB has got it won! lol
I just happen to be a "baby fish" magnet!
My PB muskie....
LOLOL...yup i think GB has it in the bag so far, love the way your still trying to lip hold it GB

I can beat GB's fish as soon as I find the pic. I had a 2 inch smallmouth hold onto my worm and not let go until it was in the boat.  It was way smaller than my worm. I love teh sunfish slammin the husky jerks/x-raps.  I throw husky jerk 12s all the time on simcoe and catch tons of perch.  Too funny
The whole expresion and pose of GB and his fish is priceless.
Used this guy for bait 2 weeks ago
Ok this little smallmouth could just get his mouth over the worm.  Once he did so he couldn't let go.  Smallest fish I have ever actually caught on a rod and reel.

Now we are going to need a thread on the proper method to hold these minny monsters.  The tackle manufactures need to jump on this new niche market. I see miniature cradles and scales in grams.  I've always tried to hide these fish from the camera, now I see I should be regaling in them. Great shots guys and gals.
